  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study evaluates the effect of external diaphragmatic pacemaker on the patients with
      chronic cor pulmonale. Half of participants will receive external diaphragmatic pacemaker,
      while the other half will receive routine therapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Investigate the effect of external diaphragmatic pacemaker on chronic cor pulmonale, the
      indicators include: respiratory muscle force, diaphragmatic degree of excursion and
      thickness, pulmonary artery pressure, respiratory distress, feeling of fatigue and quality of
      life, pulmonary function,NT-proBNP,PaO2 and PaCO2.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
